# Multi-Environment Pipeline

##    Jenkins Pipelien - Deploy to Multiple Environments
You will learn how to **define multiple environemnt deployment is one pipeline**.

pipeline {
    agent any
    environemnt {
        INSTITUTE_NAME = "Pathnex"
    }
    stages {
        stage('Deploy to Dev') {
            steps {
                sh 'echo "Deploying $INSTITUTE_NAME to Dev environment"'
            }
        }
        stage('Deploy to Staging') {
            steps {
                input message: "Approve Staging Deployment?"
                sh 'echo "Deploying $INSTITUTE_NAME to Staging enviurnment"'
            }
        }
         stage('Deploy to Prod') {
            steps {
                input message: "Approve Prod Deployment?"
                sh 'echo "Deploying $INSTITUTE_NAME to Prod environment"'
            }
        }
    }
}

##    GitLab CI - Multi-Environment
You will learn how to **define multiple environment deployments in GitLa CI**.

stages:
  - deploy

variables:
  INSTITUTE_NAME: "Pathnex"

deploy-dev:
  stage: deploy
  image: alpine:latest
  script:
    - echo "Deploying $INSTITUTE_NAME to Dev environment"

deploy-staging:
  stage: deploy
  image: alpine:latest
  script:
    - echo "Deploying $INSTITUTE_NAME to Staging environment"
  when: manual

deploy-prod:
  stage: deploy
  image: alphne:latest
  script:
    - echo "Deploying $INSTITUTE_NAME to Prod enviourment"
  when: manual
